.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:702:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:671:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6455940/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nPrimary site navigation \n![Close](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons/close.svg) Search  ![Search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6455940/)\nLogged in as: \n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n\n[](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ \"Home\")\n![PMC search open icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) ![PMC search close ison](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/close.svg)\nSearch PMC Full-Text Archive Search in PMC ![Search](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons-bg/search--white.svg)\n  * [ Journal List ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/journals/)\n  * [ User Guide ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/userguide/)\n\n  * ![Open resources icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/more_vert.svg)\n  * [ ![View on publisher site icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/launch.svg) ](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41370-018-0099-9)View on publisher site\n  * [ ![Download PDF icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/file_download.svg) ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6455940/pdf/41370_2018_Article_99.pdf)Download PDF\n  * ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-full.svg) ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-empty.svg) Add to Collections\n  * ![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![Nature Portfolio logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-npgopen.png)\nJ Expo Sci Environ Epidemiol\n. 2019 Jan 8;29(2):157–171. doi: [10.1038/s41370-018-0099-9](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41370-018-0099-9)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"J%20Expo%20Sci%20Environ%20Epidemiol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"J%20Expo%20Sci%20Environ%20Epidemiol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"J%20Expo%20Sci%20Environ%20Epidemiol\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6455940/?term=\"J%20Expo%20Sci%20Environ%20Epidemiol\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Guideline levels for PFOA and PFOS in drinking water: the role of scientific uncertainty, risk assessment decisions, and social factors\n[Alissa Cordner](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Cordner%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n### Alissa Cordner\n1Department of Sociology, Whitman College, Walla Walla, WA USA \nFind articles by [Alissa Cordner](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Cordner%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n1,✉, [Vanessa Y De La Rosa](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"De%20La%20Rosa%20VY\"\\[Author\\])\n### Vanessa Y De La Rosa\n2Silent Spring Institute, Newton, MA USA \n3Department of Sociology and Anthropology, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \nFind articles by [Vanessa Y De La Rosa](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"De%20La%20Rosa%20VY\"\\[Author\\])\n2,3, [Laurel A Schaider](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Schaider%20LA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Laurel A Schaider\n2Silent Spring Institute, Newton, MA USA \nFind articles by [Laurel A Schaider](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Schaider%20LA\"\\[Author\\])\n2, [Ruthann A Rudel](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rudel%20RA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Ruthann A Rudel\n2Silent Spring Institute, Newton, MA USA \nFind articles by [Ruthann A Rudel](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rudel%20RA\"\\[Author\\])\n2, [Lauren Richter](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Richter%20L\"\\[Author\\])\n### Lauren Richter\n3Department of Sociology and Anthropology, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \nFind articles by [Lauren Richter](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Richter%20L\"\\[Author\\])\n3, [Phil Brown](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Brown%20P\"\\[Author\\])\n### Phil Brown\n3Department of Sociology and Anthropology, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \n4Department of Health Sciences, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \nFind articles by [Phil Brown](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Brown%20P\"\\[Author\\])\n3,4\n  * Author information\n  * Article notes\n  * Copyright and License information\n\n1Department of Sociology, Whitman College, Walla Walla, WA USA \n2Silent Spring Institute, Newton, MA USA \n3Department of Sociology and Anthropology, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \n4Department of Health Sciences, Northeastern University, Boston, MA USA \n✉\nCorresponding author.\nReceived 2018 Jul 30; Revised 2018 Oct 21; Accepted 2018 Nov 12; Issue date 2019.\n© The Author(s) 2019\n**Open Access** This article is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License, which permits use, sharing, adaptation, distribution and reproduction in any medium or format, as long as you give appropriate credit to the original author(s) and the source, provide a link to the Creative Commons license, and indicate if changes were made. The images or other third party material in this article are included in the article’s Creative Commons license, unless indicated otherwise in a credit line to the material. If material is not included in the article’s Creative Commons license and your intended use is not permitted by statutory regulation or exceeds the permitted use, you will need to obtain permission directly from the copyright holder. To view a copy of this license, visit <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/>.\n[PMC Copyright notice](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\nPMCID: PMC6455940 NIHMSID: [NIHMS1512873](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/mid/NIHMS1512873/) PMID: [30622333](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30622333/)\n**This article has been corrected.** See [J Expo Sci Environ Epidemiol. 2019 Mar 29;29(6):861](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6803515/).\n**This article has been corrected.** See [J Expo Sci Environ Epidemiol. 2020 Feb 6;30(3):585](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8076034/).\n##  Abstract\nCommunities across the U.S. are discovering drinking water contaminated by perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) and determining appropriate actions. There are currently no federal PFAS drinking water standards despite widespread drinking water contamination, ubiquitous population-level exposure, and toxicological and epidemiological evidence of adverse health effects. Absent federal PFAS standards, multiple U.S. states have developed their own health-based water guideline levels to guide decisions about contaminated site cleanup and drinking water surveillance and treatment. We examined perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA) and perfluorooctane sulfonate (PFOS) water guideline levels developed by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and state agencies to protect people drinking"
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:705:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:721:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nP