![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![Environmental Health Perspectives logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-envhper.png)\nEnviron Health Perspect\n. 2020 Nov 11;128(11):114002. doi: [10.1289/EHP7853](https://doi.org/10.1289/EHP7853)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"Environ%20Health%20Perspect\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Environ%20Health%20Perspect\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"Environ%20Health%20Perspect\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/?term=\"Environ%20Health%20Perspect\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Breaking It Down: Estimating Short-Chain PFAS Half-Lives in a Human Population\n[Wendee Nicole](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Nicole%20W\"\\[Author\\])\n### Wendee Nicole\nFind articles by [Wendee Nicole](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Nicole%20W\"\\[Author\\])\n✉\n  * Author information\n  * Article notes\n  * Copyright and License information\n\n✉\nCorresponding author.\nReceived 2020 Jul 7; Accepted 2020 Jul 9; Collection date 2020 Nov.\n_EHP_ is an open-access journal published with support from the National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences, National Institutes of Health. All content is public domain unless otherwise noted.\n[PMC Copyright notice](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\nPMCID: PMC7657368 PMID: [33174763](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33174763/)\nSee \"[Serum Half-Lives for Short- and Long-Chain Perfluoroalkyl Acids after Ceasing Exposure from Drinking Water Contaminated by Firefighting Foam](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7351026/)\", 077004.\n##  Abstract\n![A firefighter spraying foam at a jet](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/blobs/93d2/7657368/e4d845e44e11/ehp7853_abstract.jpg)\n[Open in a new tab](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/figure/d40e81/)\n* * *\nMany studies have examined the impact of long-chain per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) on human health,[1](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c1) but few have looked at short-chain PFAS.[2](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c2) A recent study in _Environmental Health Perspectives_ estimated half-lives of both long- and short-chain PFAS in a small group of people immediately after exposure to PFAS-contaminated drinking water ended.[3](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c3)\n![A firefighter spraying foam at a jet](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/blobs/93d2/7657368/cbaf044ed924/ehp7853_f1.jpg)\n[Open in a new tab](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/figure/f1/)\nThe same chemistry that makes PFAS so persistent in the environment also enables them to quickly extinguish fires. Firefighting foam spreads and forms a film over the fire, smothering the flames and cooling the fuel. Image: © Dushlik/Shutterstock.\nThe terms “long” and “short” refer to the length of the carbon (C) backbone of each molecule; long-chain is defined as perfluoroalkyl sulfonic acids with 6 or more C atoms, and perfluoroalkyl carboxylic acids with 7 or more C atoms.[4](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c4) Most long-chain PFAS have been phased out and replaced by short-chain varieties. Thus, long-chain varieties are sometimes called legacy PFAS.\nIt is generally believed that the shorter the chain, the shorter the half-life for PFAS.[2](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c2) However, this rapid excretion also makes it difficult to assess the health impacts of short-chain varieties because studies may start weeks or months after exposure has ceased.\n“For an observational study of half-life in humans, it is crucial to find a proper population with a defined end of external exposure,” says lead author Yiyi Xu, a research associate at the University of Gothenburg in Sweden. “Due to faster elimination of short-chain PFAS, researchers need to start the observation as soon as the external exposure stops, to capture reasonable serum levels for half-life estimation.” Only a handful of previous studies have quantified the half-lives of short-chain PFAS in human populations.[5](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c5),[6](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c6),[7](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c7),[8](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c8)\nThe new study took place at Sweden’s Arvidsjaur regional airport, which has its own drinking water supply, separate from the municipality of Arvidsjaur. The airport water source was contaminated with PFAS, presumably from aqueous film-forming foam used at an on-site fire drill area. Some firefighting foams contain fluorinated surfactants and are a known source of both long- and short-chain PFAS pollution.[9](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7657368/#c9)\nWhen authorities discovered the water contamination at the airport in August 2018, they immediately provided clean water to employees and then contacted the authors of the new paper to quantify exposure levels. The researchers sampled serum and urine for 17 airport employees starting 11–14 days after exposure ended. The municipal supply had very low levels of PFAS, which enabled the researchers to confirm that employees"
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:707:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:741:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12020356/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nPrimary site navigation \n![Close](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons/close.svg) Search  ![Search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12020356/)\nLogged in as: \n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n\n[](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ \"Home\")\n![PMC search open icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) ![PMC search close ison](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/close.svg)\nSearch PMC Full-Text Archive Search in PMC ![Search](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons-bg/search--white.svg)\n  * [ Journal List ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/journals/)\n  * [ User Guide ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/userguide/)\n\n  * ![Open resources icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/more_vert.svg)\n  * [ ![View on publisher site icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/launch.svg) ](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.4c13284)View on publisher site\n  * [ ![Download PDF icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/file_download.svg) ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12020356/pdf/es4c13284.pdf)Download PDF\n  * ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-full.svg) ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-empty.svg) Add to Collections\n  * ![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![ACS AuthorChoice logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-acssd.png)\nEnviron Sci Technol\n. 2025 Apr 11;59(15):7678–7687. doi: [10.1021/acs.est.4c13284](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.4c13284)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12020356/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Modeling PFAS Sorption in Soils Using Machine Learning\n[Joel Fabregat-Palau](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Fabregat-Palau%20J\"\\[Author\\])\n### Joel Fabregat-Palau\n†Department of Geosciences, University of Tübingen, Schnarrenbergstraße 94-96, Tübingen 72076, Germany\nFind articles by [Joel Fabregat-Palau](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Fabregat-Palau%20J\"\\[Author\\])\n†,*, [Amirhossein Ershadi](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Ershadi%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n### Amirhossein Ershadi\n†Department of Geosciences, University of Tübingen, Schnarrenbergstraße 94-96, Tübingen 72076, Germany\nFind articles by [Amirhossein Ershadi](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Ershadi%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n†,*, [Michael Finkel](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Finkel%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n### Michael Finkel\n†Department of Geosciences, University of Tübingen, Schnarrenbergstraße 94-96, Tübingen 72076, Germany\nFind articles by [Michael Finkel](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Finkel%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n†, [Anna Rigol](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rigol%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n### Anna Rigol\n‡Department of Chemical Engineering and Analytical Chemistry, University of Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1-11, Barcelona 08028, Spain\n§Institut de Recerca de l’Aigua (IdRA), Universitat de Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1-11, Barcelona 08028, Spain\nFind articles by [Anna Rigol](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rigol%20A\"\\[Author\\])\n‡,§, [Miquel Vidal](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Vidal%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n### Miquel Vidal\n‡Department of Chemical Engineering and Analytical Chemistry, University of Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1-11, Barcelona 08028, Spain\nFind articles by [Miquel Vidal](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Vidal%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n‡, [Peter Grathwohl](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Grathwohl%20P\"\\[Author\\])\n### Peter Grathwohl\n†Department of Geosciences, University of Tübingen, Schnarrenbergstraße 94-96, Tübingen 72076, Germany\nFind articles by [Peter Grathwohl](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Grathwohl%20P\"\\[Author\\])\n†\n  * Author information\n  * Article notes\n  * Copyright and License information\n\n†Department of Geosciences, University of Tübingen, Schnarrenbergstraße 94-96, Tübingen 72076, Germany\n‡Department of Chemical Engineering and Analytical Chemistry, University of Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1-11, Barcelona 08028, Spain\n§Institut de Recerca de l’Aigua (IdRA), Universitat de Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1-11, Barcelona 08028, Spain\n*\nE-mail: joel.fabregat-palau@uni-tuebingen.de.\n*\nE-mail: amirhossein.ershadi@uni-tuebingen.de.\nReceived 2024 Nov 28; Accepted 2025 Mar 31; Revised 2025 Mar 29; Collection date 2025 Apr 22.\n© 2025 The Authors. Published by American Chemical Society\nPermits the broadest form of re-use including for commercial purposes, provided that author attribution and integrity are maintained (<https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/>).\n[PMC Copyright notice](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\nPMCID: PMC12020356 PMID: [40215413](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40215413/)\n##  Abstract\n![graphic file with name es4c13284_0006.jpg](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/blobs/5c58/12020356/9fc51de0fb93/es4c13284_0006.jpg)\nIn this study, we introduce PFASorptionML, a novel machine learning (ML) tool developed to predict solid–liquid distribution coefficients (_K_ d) for per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) in soils. Leveraging a data set of 1,274 _K_ d entries for PFAS in soils and sediments, including compounds such as trifluoroacetate, cationic, and zwitterionic PFAS, and neutral fluorotelomer alcohols, the model incorporates PFAS-specific properties such as molecular weight, hydrophobicity, and p _K_ a, alongside soil characteristics like pH, texture, organic carbon content, and cation exchange capacity. Sensitivity analysis reveals that molecular weight, hydrophobicity, and organic carbon content are the most significant factors influencing sorption behavior, while charge density and mineral soil fraction have comparatively minor effects. The model demonstrates high predictive performance, with RPD values exceeding 3.16 across validation data sets, outperforming existing tools in accuracy and scope. Notably, PFAS chain length and functional group variability significantly influence _K_ d, with longer chain lengths and higher hydrophobicity positively correlating with _K_ d. By integrating location-specific soil repository data, the model enables the generation of spatial _K_ d maps for selected PFAS species. These capabilities are implemented in the online platform PFASorptionML, providin"
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:708:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:756:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11962083/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nPrimary site navigation \n![Close](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons/close.svg) Search  ![Search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11962083/)\nLogged in as: \n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n\n[](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ \"Home\")\n![PMC search open icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) ![PMC search close ison](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/close.svg)\nSearch PMC Full-Text Archive Search in PMC ![Search](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons-bg/search--white.svg)\n  * [ Journal List ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/journals/)\n  * [ User Guide ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/userguide/)\n\n  * ![Open resources icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/more_vert.svg)\n  * [ ![View on publisher site icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/launch.svg) ](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-025-58040-w)View on publisher site\n  * [ ![Download PDF icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/file_download.svg) ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11962083/pdf/41467_2025_Article_58040.pdf)Download PDF\n  * ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-full.svg) ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-empty.svg) Add to Collections\n  * ![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![Nature Communications logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-ncomms.gif)\nNat Commun\n. 2025 Apr 1;16:3118. doi: [10.1038/s41467-025-58040-w](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-025-58040-w)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"Nat%20Commun\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Nat%20Commun\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"Nat%20Commun\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11962083/?term=\"Nat%20Commun\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Mineralogical controls on PFAS and anthropogenic anions in subsurface soils and aquifers\n[Marina G Evich](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Evich%20MG\"\\[Author\\])\n### Marina G Evich\n1USEPA, Office of Research and Development, Center for Environmental Measurement and Modeling, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Marina G Evich](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Evich%20MG\"\\[Author\\])\n1,✉, [James Ferreira](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Ferreira%20J\"\\[Author\\])\n### James Ferreira\n2USEPA, Region 4, Atlanta, GA USA \nFind articles by [James Ferreira](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Ferreira%20J\"\\[Author\\])\n2, [Oluwaseun Adeyemi](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Adeyemi%20O\"\\[Author\\])\n### Oluwaseun Adeyemi\n3Department of Geology, University of Georgia, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Oluwaseun Adeyemi](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Adeyemi%20O\"\\[Author\\])\n3, [Paul A Schroeder](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Schroeder%20PA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Paul A Schroeder\n3Department of Geology, University of Georgia, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Paul A Schroeder](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Schroeder%20PA\"\\[Author\\])\n3, [Jason C Williams](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Williams%20JC\"\\[Author\\])\n### Jason C Williams\n4South Carolina Department of Health and Environmental Control, Bureau of Land and Waste Management, Columbia, SC USA \nFind articles by [Jason C Williams](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Williams%20JC\"\\[Author\\])\n4, [Brad Acrey](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Acrey%20B\"\\[Author\\])\n### Brad Acrey\n5USEPA, Region 4, Laboratory Services and Applied Sciences Division, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Brad Acrey](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Acrey%20B\"\\[Author\\])\n5, [Diana Burdette](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Burdette%20D\"\\[Author\\])\n### Diana Burdette\n5USEPA, Region 4, Laboratory Services and Applied Sciences Division, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Diana Burdette](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Burdette%20D\"\\[Author\\])\n5, [Malcolm Grieve](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Grieve%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n### Malcolm Grieve\n5USEPA, Region 4, Laboratory Services and Applied Sciences Division, Athens, GA USA \nFind articles by [Malcolm Grieve](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Grie