.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:709:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:781:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8760172/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nPrimary site navigation \n![Close](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons/close.svg) Search  ![Search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8760172/)\nLogged in as: \n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n\n[](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ \"Home\")\n![PMC search open icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) ![PMC search close ison](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/close.svg)\nSearch PMC Full-Text Archive Search in PMC ![Search](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons-bg/search--white.svg)\n  * [ Journal List ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/journals/)\n  * [ User Guide ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/userguide/)\n\n  * ![Open resources icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/more_vert.svg)\n  * [ ![View on publisher site icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/launch.svg) ](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.envres.2021.112433)View on publisher site\n  * [ ![Download PDF icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/file_download.svg) ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8760172/pdf/nihms-1763191.pdf)Download PDF\n  * ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-full.svg) ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-empty.svg) Add to Collections\n  * ![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![NIHPA Author Manuscripts logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-nihpa.png)\nEnviron Res\n. Author manuscript; available in PMC: 2023 Apr 1.\n_Published in final edited form as:_ Environ Res. 2021 Dec 4;205:112433. doi: [10.1016/j.envres.2021.112433](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.envres.2021.112433)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"Environ%20Res\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Environ%20Res\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"Environ%20Res\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8760172/?term=\"Environ%20Res\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Montmorillonite clay-based sorbents decrease the bioavailability of per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) from soil and their translocation to plants\n[Sara E Hearon](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Hearon%20SE\"\\[Author\\])\n### Sara E Hearon\naVeterinary Integrative Biosciences Department, College of Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX, USA 77845\nFind articles by [Sara E Hearon](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Hearon%20SE\"\\[Author\\])\na, [Asuka A Orr](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Orr%20AA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Asuka A Orr\nbArtie McFerrin Department of Chemical Engineering, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX 77843, USA\nFind articles by [Asuka A Orr](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Orr%20AA\"\\[Author\\])\nb, [Haley Moyer](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Moyer%20H\"\\[Author\\])\n### Haley Moyer\naVeterinary Integrative Biosciences Department, College of Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX, USA 77845\nFind articles by [Haley Moyer](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Moyer%20H\"\\[Author\\])\na, [Meichen Wang](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Wang%20M\"\\[Author\\])\n### Meichen Wang\naVeterinary Integrative Biosciences Department, College of Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX, USA 77845\nFind articles by [Meichen Wang](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Wang%20M\"\\[Author\\])\na, [Phanourios Tamamis](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Tamamis%20P\"\\[Author\\])\n### Phanourios Tamamis\nbArtie McFerrin Department of Chemical Engineering, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX 77843, USA\ncDepartment of Materials Science and Engineering, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX 77843, USA\nFind articles by [Phanourios Tamamis](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Tamamis%20P\"\\[Author\\])\nb,c, [Timothy D Phillips](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Phillips%20TD\"\\[Author\\])\n### Timothy D Phillips\naVeterinary Integrative Biosciences Department, College of Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX, USA 77845\nFind articles by [Timothy D Phillips](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Phillips%20TD\"\\[Author\\])\na,*\n  * Author information\n  * Article notes\n  * Copyright and License information\n\naVeterinary Integrative Biosciences Department, College of Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX, USA 77845\nbArtie McFerrin Department of Chemical Engineering, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX 77843, USA\ncDepartment of Materials Science and Engineering, Texas A&M University, College Station, TX 77843, USA\n*\nAddress correspondence to Timothy D. Phillips, 4458 TAMU, College Station, TX. 77843-4458; Phone: 979-229-1585, tphillips@cvm.tamu.edu\nIssue date 2022 Apr 1.\n[PMC Copyright notice](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\nPMCID: PMC8760172 NIHMSID: NIHMS1763191 PMID: [34875259](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34875259/)\nThe publisher's version of this article is available at [Environ Res](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.envres.2021.112433)\n##  Abstract\nConsumption of food and water contaminated with per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) presents a significant risk for human exposure. There is limited data on high affinity sorbents that can be used to reduce the bioavailability of PFAS from soil and translocation to plants and garden produce. To address this need, montmorillonite clay was amended with the nutrients carnitine and choline to increase the hydrophobicity of the sorbent and the interlayer spacing. In this study, the binding of PFOA (perfluorooctanoic acid) and PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid) to parent and amended clays was characterized. Isothermal analyses were conducted at pH 7 and ambient temperature (to simulate environmentally-relevant conditions). The data for all tested sorbents fit the Langmuir model indicating saturable binding sites with high capacities and affinities under neutral conditions. Amended montmorillonite clays had increased capacities for PFOA and PFOS (0.51 – 0.71 mol kg−1) compared to the parent clay (0.37 – 0.49 mol kg−1). Molecular dynamics (MD) simulations suggested that hydrophobic and electrostatic interactions at the terminal fluorinated carbon chains of PFAS compounds were major modes of surface interaction. The safety and efficacy of the clays were confirmed in a living organism (_Lemna minor_), where clays (at 0.1% inclusion) allowed for increase"
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:711:outputs\campaigns\CAMP_20260310T073230_fb78bf\WEB_20260310T073230_5da0fc.json:831:      "content": "[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9724633/#main-content)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg)\nAn official website of the United States government \nHere's how you know\nHere's how you know\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg)\n**Official websites use .gov**   \nA **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg)\n**Secure .gov websites use HTTPS**   \nA **lock** (  Lock Locked padlock icon  ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. \n[ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/)\n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search \n![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/person.svg) Log in ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_less.svg) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/expand_more.svg)\n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n  * Log out \n\nSearch…  Search NCBI \nPrimary site navigation \n![Close](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons/close.svg) Search  ![Search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9724633/)\nLogged in as: \n  * [ Dashboard ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/)\n  * [ Publications ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/myncbi/collections/bibliography/)\n  * [ Account settings ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/)\n\n[](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ \"Home\")\n![PMC search open icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) ![PMC search close ison](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/close.svg)\nSearch PMC Full-Text Archive Search in PMC ![Search](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/usa-icons-bg/search--white.svg)\n  * [ Journal List ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/journals/)\n  * [ User Guide ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/userguide/)\n\n  * ![Open resources icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/more_vert.svg)\n  * [ ![View on publisher site icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/launch.svg) ](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.0c08506)View on publisher site\n  * [ ![Download PDF icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/file_download.svg) ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9724633/pdf/nihms-1849378.pdf)Download PDF\n  * ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-full.svg) ![Collections icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/action-bookmark-empty.svg) Add to Collections\n  * ![Cite icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/format_quote.svg) Cite\n  * ![Show article permalink icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/share.svg) Permalink\n## PERMALINK\n![Copy icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/content_copy.svg) Copy\n\n![Open article navigation icon](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/list.svg)\nAs a library, NLM provides access to scientific literature. Inclusion in an NLM database does not imply endorsement of, or agreement with, the contents by NLM or the National Institutes of Health.  \nLearn more: [PMC Disclaimer](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/disclaimer/) | [ PMC Copyright Notice ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/copyright/)\n![NIST Author Manuscripts logo](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/banners/logo-nistpa.png)\nEnviron Sci Technol\n. Author manuscript; available in PMC: 2022 Dec 6.\n_Published in final edited form as:_ Environ Sci Technol. 2021 May 13;55(11):7237–7245. doi: [10.1021/acs.est.0c08506](https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.0c08506)\n  * [Search in PMC](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/search/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [Search in PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n  * [View in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[Title%20Abbreviation\\])\n  * [Add to search](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9724633/?term=\"Environ%20Sci%20Technol\"\\[jour\\])\n\n# Environmental Source Tracking of Per- and Polyfluoroalkyl Substances within a Forensic Context: Current and Future Techniques\n[Joseph A Charbonnet](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Charbonnet%20JA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Joseph A Charbonnet\n1Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Colorado School of Mines, Golden, Colorado 80401, United States\nFind articles by [Joseph A Charbonnet](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Charbonnet%20JA\"\\[Author\\])\n1,‡, [Alix E Rodowa](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rodowa%20AE\"\\[Author\\])\n### Alix E Rodowa\n2Biochemical and Exposure Science Group, National Institute of Standards & Technology, Charleston, South Carolina 29412, United States\nFind articles by [Alix E Rodowa](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Rodowa%20AE\"\\[Author\\])\n2,‡, [Nayantara T Joseph](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Joseph%20NT\"\\[Author\\])\n### Nayantara T Joseph\n3School of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Cornell University, Ithaca, New York 14853-0001, United States\nFind articles by [Nayantara T Joseph](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Joseph%20NT\"\\[Author\\])\n3, [Jennifer L Guelfo](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Guelfo%20JL\"\\[Author\\])\n### Jennifer L Guelfo\n4Department of Civil, Environmental, and Construction Engineering, Texas Tech University, Lubbock, Texas 79409, United States\nFind articles by [Jennifer L Guelfo](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Guelfo%20JL\"\\[Author\\])\n4, [Jennifer A Field](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Field%20JA\"\\[Author\\])\n### Jennifer A Field\n5Department of Environmental and Molecular Toxicology, Oregon State University, Corvallis, Oregon 97331-7301, United States\nFind articles by [Jennifer A Field](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Field%20JA\"\\[Author\\])\n5, [Gerrad D Jones](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Jones%20GD\"\\[Author\\])\n### Gerrad D Jones\n6Department of Biological and Ecological Engineering, Oregon State University, Corvallis, Oregon 97331, United States\nFind articles by [Gerrad D Jones](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Jones%20GD\"\\[Author\\])\n6, [Christopher P Higgins](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Higgins%20CP\"\\[Author\\])\n### Christopher P Higgins\n7Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Colorado School of Mines, Golden, Colorado 80401, United States\nFind articles by [Christopher P Higgins](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Higgins%20CP\"\\[Author\\])\n7, [Damian E Helbling](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Helbling%20DE\"\\[Author\\])\n### Damian E Helbling\n8School of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Cornell University, Ithaca, New York 14853-0001, United States\nFind articles by [Damian E Helbling](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Helbling%20DE\"\\[Author\\])\n8, [Erika F Houtz](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Houtz%20EF\"\\[Author\\])\n### Erika F Houtz\n9Arcadis, San Francisco, California 94104, United States\nFind articles by [Erika F Houtz](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=\"Houtz%20EF\"\\[Author\\])\n9\n  * Author information\n  * Article notes\n  * Copyright and License information\n\n1Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Colorado School of Mines, Golden, Colorado 80401, United States\n2Biochemical and Exposure Science Group, National Institute of Standards & Technology, Charleston, South Carolina 29412, United States\n3School of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Cornell University, Ithaca, New York 14853-0001, United States\n4Department of Civil, Environmental, and Construction Engineering, Texas Tech University, Lubbock, Texas 79409, United States\n5Department of Environmental and Molecular Toxicology, Oregon State University, Corvallis, Oregon 97331-7301, United States\n6Department of Biological and Ecological Engineering, Oregon State University, Corvallis, Oregon 97331, United States\n7Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Colorado School of Mines, Golden, Colorado 80401, United States\n8School of Civil and Environmental Engineering, Cornell University, Ithaca, New York 14853-0001, United States\n9Arcadis, San Francisco, California 94104, United States\n‡\nAuthor Contributions\nJ.A.C. and A.E.R