.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:1707:outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_9\codex_stderr.log:3036:Citation binding: V17 has strong visible citation markers and a bibliography with tier labels. It uses some primary RCTs well: NEJM SURPASS-2 [1], Lancet SURPASS-3 [2], Lancet SURPASS-4 [21], NEJM SURPASS-CVOT [16]. But in body prose it often binds broad safety claims to systematic reviews or pharmacovigilance rather than regulatory labels or primary trial adverse-event tables (line 9). For SURPASS-CVOT, the body cites both baseline/design [23] and a news article [24] for outcome interpretation (line 21), despite a primary NEJM CVOT source being present in the bibliography [16].
