.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:2128:outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_3\findings.md:85:3. SURPASS-5 mis-tiering: The JAMA SURPASS-5 randomized clinical trial is classified T7 in corpus output. That classification is materially wrong and likely prevents proper use.
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:2135:outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_10\findings.md:7:   reason: V21 retrieves the broadest and most regulator-specific set: FDA Mounjaro NDA summary and clinical pharmacology reviews, FDA Mounjaro label, FDA Zepbound NDA/label/press material, EMA EPAR/product information/variation assessment reports, NICE TA924 documents and rollout article, and a Canadian Product Monograph (report.md:21,82-96). ChatGPT cites FDA statistical review, U.S. prescribing information, and EMA product information but not NICE or Health Canada (compare_chatgpt_dr.txt:51-52,966-981,1135-1166). Gemini cites FDA labels and multiple Health Canada/Canadian safety sources, but not EMA or NICE (compare_gemini_dr.txt:828-857).
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:2136:outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_10\findings.md:9:   reason: V21 usually attributes regulatory claims to the specific authority: FDA approval/dosing/boxed warning, EMA EU marketing authorization and indication, NICE criteria, and Canadian Product Monograph contraindication/warnings (report.md:21). It has one broad sentence that "key labeling warnings and precautions are consistent across authorities" (report.md:21), which is less precise than ChatGPT's explicit warning that U.S. and EU texts are not interchangeable (compare_chatgpt_dr.txt:35-49,974-981). Gemini is weaker: it says updates were issued by "both" FDA and Health Canada (compare_gemini_dr.txt:30-32), says "Both FDA and Health Canada guidelines mandate" dose-reduction consideration without separating label language (compare_gemini_dr.txt:530-532), and extrapolates a Health Canada perioperative review into global protocol shifts and withholding practices (compare_gemini_dr.txt:596-603). V21 therefore beats Gemini but not ChatGPT.
