.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:2144:outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_10\findings.md:30:V21's regulatory retrieval is genuinely strong and broader than both competitors, especially because it includes NICE and EMA documents as well as FDA and Canadian material. That advantage is not enough to terminate the loop because V21 loses to both competitors on trial framing, structure, and narrative depth. The advisory manifest flags should not drive the verdict; the content-level issue is that V21 reads like a compact evidence synthesis, while the competitors read like full deep-research reports.
