.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:4229:+| 2. Regulatory | **BEAT_BOTH** | V27 Regulatory is dense and primary-regulator anchored: FDA Mounjaro/Zepbound approvals, dose escalation, boxed warning, contraindications, retinopathy/aspiration/KwikPen warnings at report line 25 with FDA sources [35]-[39] lines 98-102 (`accessdata.fda.gov`, `fda.gov`); EMA authorization, pediatric/T2D language, weight-management indication, additional monitoring, SmPC warnings with [40]-[42] lines 103-105 (`ema.europa.eu`); Health Canada product monographs [43]-[44] lines 106-107 (`https://pdf.hres.ca/dpd_pm/00073189.PDF`, `00083504.PDF`); NICE T2D and obesity guidance [45]-[47] lines 108-110 (`nice.org.uk`). ChatGPT is mostly FDA/EMA prescribing at compare lines 968-982. Gemini is deep on FDA/Health Canada safety updates and counterfeit risk at compare lines 530-639, but lacks NICE. V27's four-jurisdiction regulator span beats both on breadth and is close enough on depth because it includes KwikPen, aspiration, HC monographs, and NICE stopping/titration rules. |
.\outputs\codex_findings\dr_output_pass_14_v27\_codex_stdout.txt:4230:+| 3. Jurisdictional | **BEAT_BOTH** | V27 names and differentiates US FDA, EMA, Health Canada, and NICE in one regulatory paragraph, not just boilerplate. NICE criteria include BMI thresholds, occupational insulin implications, ethnic-threshold adjustment, tirzepatide titration, and 6-month 5% stopping rule at report line 25 with NICE URLs [45]-[47]. Health Canada content is label-specific: Canadian indication and serious-warnings box at report line 25 with product monograph URLs [43]-[44]. ChatGPT has US/EMA label comparison only at compare lines 968-982. Gemini has strong Health Canada specificity at lines 530-539 and 584-639, but no NICE. V27 therefore beats ChatGPT on non-US spread and beats Gemini on jurisdictional spread, despite Gemini's Canada depth. |
