.\outputs\codex_findings\autoloop_v2_protocol_review\_codex_stdout.txt:280:   reason: V23 has 31 bibliography entries with reasonable domain diversity, including Springer/PMC/Nature/FDA/EMA/NICE/Frontiers/Cureus, but the report itself admits only 16% T1 primary studies and the bibliography foregrounds post-hoc, indirect-comparison, NMA, and regulatory sources rather than the core SURPASS-1 through SURPASS-6 primary trial publications (report.md lines 25 and 59-90; bibliography.json lines 1-219). ChatGPT explicitly prioritizes core SURPASS publications and lists direct SURPASS primary URLs, albeit messily duplicated, while Gemini has 42 works cited and covers SURPASS-1 through SURPASS-6 plus Health Canada/FDA items, so V23 does not beat either on count plus primary-trial coverage (state/compare_chatgpt_dr.txt lines 50-66 and 1129-1221; state/compare_gemini_dr.txt lines 680-858).
