 - Method of Cross-Linking Hyaluronic Acid with Divinylsulfone - Google Patents US20130338100A1 - Method of Cross-Linking Hyaluronic Acid with Divinylsulfone - Google Patents Method of Cross-Linking Hyaluronic Acid with Divinylsulfone Download PDF Info Publication number US20130338100A1 US20130338100A1 US13/912,894 US201313912894A US2013338100A1 US 20130338100 A1 US20130338100 A1 US 20130338100A1 US 201313912894 A US201313912894 A US 201313912894A US 2013338100 A1 US2013338100 A1 \n  Perspectives: none tagged\n  Key facts: none extracted\n\nNEW SEARCH RESULTS (round 2, titles only — not yet read):\n- Comparison of the Effectiveness of Four Different ...\n- Adhesion properties of polypropylene fabric treated with ...\n- Enhancement of Polypropylene Bonding Through Plasma ... - PMC\n- Improvement of paint adhesion to a polypropylene bumper by ...\n- How Plasma Treatment Can Improve The Adhesion Of ...\n- Quantifying Enhanced Wettability and Time-dependency of Plasma ...\n- Adhesion in Industry: Improve Bonding with Plasma Technology\n- Plasma treatment application to improve interfacial adhesion in ...\n- [PDF] Adhesion studies of the atmospheric pressure plasma treated ...\n- (PDF) Plasma‐induced surface modification and adhesion ...\n- Improving Interlayer Adhesion of Poly(p-phenylene terephthalamide ...\n- Adhesive Performance at Polymer–Substrate Interfaces in ...\n- A molecular dynamics simulation study to investigate poly ...\n- Simulations of the formation and substrate adhesion of PEI/ ...\n- Atomistic Simulation of Polymer Adhesion\n- Coacervation and adhesion mechanism of PEI/TA hydrogel ...\n- Molecular Insights into the Interfacial Adhesion and Chain ...\n- Computational approaches for investigating interfacial ...\n- The Inkjet Printing of Graphene Inks on Polyimide Substrates\n- Mesoscale modelling of polymer-mediated adhesion\n\nPERSPECTIVE COVERAGE:\n  Covered (3/9): Scientific, Regulatory, Industry\n  Uncovered: Economic, Public_Health, Historical, Regional, Methodological, Emerging_Trends\n  Low coverage: Scientific, Regulatory, Industry\n\nBased on what has been READ:\n1. Decompose the research question into 5-8 sub-questions.\n   Which sub-questions have ZERO or WEAK evidence?\n   Which sub-questions are well-answered with strong evidence?\n2. What CONTRADICTIONS exist between sources? Flag conflicting evidence.\n3. What specific KNOWLEDGE GAPS remain? List them as specific factual questions\n   we CANNOT yet answer. 'none' is almost never correct for a complex research question.\n4. Rate overall confidence in accumulated knowledge: LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH with reasoning.\n5. Which perspectives need more coverage?\n6. Generate 3-6 targeted WEB queries to fill those gaps.\n7. Generate 1-3 ACADEMIC queries using precise terminology.\n8. Optionally generate 0-1 semantic EXA queries.\n9. Assess ANSWER COMPLETENESS for the research question:\n   - List specific sub-questions that remain UNANSWERED.\n   - For each answered sub-question, rate evidence strength (weak/moderate/strong).\n   - 'expanding': Major sub-questions still unanswered.\n   - 'narrowing': Most sub-questions answered, seeking confirmation/depth.\n   - 'saturated': All sub-questions answered with strong evidence.\n10. Should we continue searching?\n\nFocus on queries that address content-level gaps, not just missing URLs."}],"response_content":"{\n  \"sub_questions\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Does experimental evidence exist for DVS-crosslinked PEI/BPEI coatings specifically?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"WEAK\",\n      \"notes\": \"General crosslinking of PEI with DVS is documented (Page 5, 7), but specific adhesive coating context is unclear.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Has this coating system been applied to plasma-activated polypropylene?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\",\n      \"notes\": \"New search titles suggest plasma-PP adhesion studies exist, but no specific DVS-PEI link extracted from read pages.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Has this coating system been applied to aluminum oxide substrates?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\",\n      \"notes\": \"No specific data extracted from read pages regarding Al2O3.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"What are the measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths for this system?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\",\n      \"notes\": \"Page 3 discusses prediction of lap shear but no specific values for DVS-PEI extracted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Do molecular dynamics predictions exist for single-bond work of adhesion for DVS-PEI interfaces?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"WEAK\",\n      \"notes\": \"New titles mention MD simulations of PEI adhesion (Titles 13, 14, 15), but content not yet read.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Is there a direct comparison between experimental adhesion strength and MD predictions for this specific system?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\",\n      \"notes\": \"No evidence of direct comparison extracted from the 7 pages read.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"contradictions\": [],\n  \"knowledge_gaps\": [\n    \"Specific lap-shear or peel strength values (MPa or N/mm) for DVS-crosslinked PEI on plasma-treated PP.\",\n    \"Specific work of adhesion values (J/m^2 or kcal/mol) from MD simulations for PEI-DVS-substrate interfaces.\",\n    \"Plasma treatment parameters (power, gas, duration) used for PP activation in relevant studies.\",\n    \"DVS to PEI molar ratios used in adhesive formulations.\",\n    \"Direct quantitative comparison methodology between macroscopic adhesion tests and atomistic MD predictions.\",\n    \"Failure mode analysis (cohesive vs adhesive) for these specific coatings.\"\n  ],\n  \"confidence_rating\": \"LOW\",\n  \"confidence_reasoning\": \"Although 7 pages were marked as read, the summaries provided indicate mostly navigational pages, security checks, or generic journal homepages with 'Key facts: none extracted'. The specific data required to answer the research question (values, comparisons, specific substrate combinations) is missing from the acquired knowledge base. The new search result titles are promising but unread.\",\n  \"perspectives_needed\": [\n    \"Scientific\",\n    \"Methodological\"\n  ],\n  \"web_queries\": [\n    \"divinyl sulfone crosslinked polyethylenimine adhesive strength plasma polypropylene\",\n    \"PEI DVS coating lap shear strength aluminum oxide plasma treatment\",\n    \"molecular dynamics simulation PEI adhesion work of adhesion comparison experiment\",\n    \"plasma activated polypropylene PEI coating adhesion test results\",\n    \"DVS crosslinked PEI hydrogel adhesion strength measurements\"\n  ],\n  \"academic_queries\": [\n    \"\\\"divinyl sulfone\\\" \\\"polyethylenimine\\\" adhesion \\\"molecular dynamics\\\"\",\n    \"\\\"PEI\\\" \\\"divinyl sulfone\\\" \\\"lap shear\\\" plasma\",\n    \"\\\"work of adhesion\\\" \\\"polyethylenimine\\\" simulation experiment comparison\"\n  ],\n  \"exa_queries\": [\n    \"experimental peel strength vs molecular dynamics prediction polyethylenimine adhesive\"\n  ],\n  \"completeness_status\": \"expanding\",\n  \"unanswered_subquestions\": [\n    \"Experimental evidence for DVS-PEI on plasma-PP.\",\n    \"Experimental evidence for DVS-PEI on Al2O3.\",\n    \"Measured peel/lap-shear strengths.\",\n    \"MD predictions of single-bond work of adhesion.\",\n    \"Comparison between experimental and MD values.\"\n  ],\n  \"answered_subquestions\": [],\n  \"continue_search\": true\n}","response_reasoning":"Thinking Process:\n\n1.  **Analyze the Request:**\n    *   **Role:** Research search strategist conducting an agentic deep research loop.\n    *   **Task:** Respond with valid JSON only (no prose, no markdown, no code fences).\n    *   **Input:** Research question, Round history (2 rounds done), Knowledge acquired (7 pages read, mostly summaries/titles without specific data extraction yet), New search results (titles only), Perspective coverage, Specific analysis tasks (1-10).\n    *   **Research Question:** What experimental evidence exists for divinyl sulfone (DVS) crosslinked polyethylenimine (PEI/BPEI) adhesive coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene and aluminum oxide substrates, and how do measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths compare with molecular dynamics predictions of single-bond work of adhesion?\n    *   **Current State:** 7 pages read, but the summaries provided in the \"Knowledge Acquired\" section are mostly generic (titles, login pages, security checks, broad journal homepages). Very little *specific* data regarding DVS-crosslinked PEI on plasma-activated PP/Al2O3 has actually been extracted from the text provided in the prompt. The \"New Search Results\" list looks promising but hasn't been read yet.\n    *   **Constraint:** Valid JSON only.\n\n2.  **Evaluate Knowledge Acquired (7 pages):**\n    *   Page 1: ACS Biomaterials Science & Engineering (Generic landing page/summary). No specific data.\n    *   Page 2: MDPI Polymers Volume 16 Issue 5 (Journal issue page). No specific data.\n    *   Page 3: MDPI Prediction of Lap Shear Strength... (Title suggests relevance, but summary is just nav links).\n    *   Page 4: ResearchGate Security Check (Failed access). No data.\n    *   Page 5: MDPI Crosslinking Approaches for PEI... (Title relevant, summary is nav links).\n    *   Page 6: ScienceDirect Relationship between structure and cytocompatibility... (Title suggests PEI/crosslinking, but summary is nav links).\n    *   Page 7: Google Patents US20130338100A1 (Hyaluronic Acid with DVS, not PEI/PP/Al2O3).\n    *   *Conclusion:* The \"Knowledge Acquired\" section is misleadingly optimistic. The summaries provided are mostly boilerplate or access denied. There is effectively *zero* specific evidence extracted regarding the specific combination (DVS + PEI + Plasma-PP/Al2O3 + MD comparison) from the text provided in the prompt. The \"New Search Results\" list contains titles that look much more relevant (e.g., \"Simulations of the formation and substrate adhesion of PEI/\", \"A molecular dynamics simulation study to investigate poly...\").\n\n3.  **Address Task Items (1-10) for JSON construction:**\n\n    *   *1. Decompose & Evidence Status:*\n        *   SQ1: Existence of DVS-crosslinked PEI coatings? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   SQ2: Use on Plasma-activated PP? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   SQ3: Use on Aluminum Oxide? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   SQ4: Measured peel/lap-shear strengths? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   SQ5: MD predictions of single-bond work of adhesion for this system? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   SQ6: Comparison between experimental and MD? (Weak/None extracted yet).\n        *   *Status:* All weak/none based on *read* content. The titles suggest potential, but content isn't ingested.\n\n    *   *2. Contradictions:* None identified yet (insufficient data).\n\n    *   *3. Knowledge Gaps:* Specific adhesion values, specific plasma treatment parameters, specific DVS/PEI ratios, specific MD simulation parameters for this interface, direct comparison studies.\n\n    *   *4. Confidence:* LOW. The summaries provided are mostly navigational or access-denied pages.\n\n    *   *5. Perspectives:* Scientific (needs depth), Methodological (needs simulation vs experiment details).\n\n    *   *6. Web Queries:* Focus on specific combinations found in new titles but not yet read.\n    *   *7. Academic Queries:* Focus on MD simulation + PEI adhesion.\n    *   *8. EXA Queries:* Semantic search for the specific comparison.\n    *   *9. Completeness:* Expanding. Major sub-questions unanswered.\n    *   *10. Continue:* Yes.\n\n4.  **Drafting the JSON:**\n    *   Must ensure strict JSON validity (escape quotes, no trailing commas).\n    *   Must reflect the reality that the previous 7 pages yielded almost no actual data despite the \"Key facts: none extracted\" notation in the prompt's input (wait, the prompt says \"Key facts: none extracted\" for most pages). I need to be honest in the analysis that the *reading* didn't yield facts, even if the *search* found titles.\n    *   The prompt asks me to act as the strategist *based on what has been READ*. Since the read content is mostly empty/boilerplate, the analysis must reflect low confidence and high gap.\n\n5.  **Refining Queries:**\n    *   Need to target the specific intersection: PEI + DVS + Plasma + PP/Al2O3 + Adhesion + MD Simulation.\n    *   The \"New Search Results\" have titles like \"Simulations of the formation and substrate adhesion of PEI/\" and \"A molecular dynamics simulation study to investigate poly...\". These need to be prioritized for reading in the next round, but I need to generate *queries* to find more if those fail or to find the specific comparison data.\n    *   Actually, the instruction says \"Generate 3-6 targeted WEB queries... Generate 1-3 ACADEMIC queries\". I should formulate queries that would find the *content* of those titles or similar specific studies.\n\n6.  **JSON Structure Plan:**\n    *   `sub_questions`: Array of objects.\n    *   `contradictions`: Array of strings.\n    *   `knowledge_gaps`: Array of strings.\n    *   `confidence_rating`: String.\n    *   `confidence_reasoning`: String.\n    *   `perspectives_needed`: Array of strings.\n    *   `web_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `academic_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `exa_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `completeness_status`: String.\n    *   `unanswered_subquestions`: Array of strings.\n    *   `answered_subquestions`: Array of objects (question, strength).\n    *   `continue_search`: Boolean.\n\n7.  **Final Review against Constraints:**\n    *   NO prose outside JSON.\n    *   NO markdown code fences (```json).\n    *   Just the raw JSON object.\n    *   Ensure all quotes are escaped properly.\n\n    *Self-Correction on \"Knowledge Acquired\":* The prompt input says \"Key facts: none extracted\" for almost all pages. This confirms my assessment that the current knowledge base is effectively empty regarding specific data points. I must not hallucinate that we know the adhesion strengths.\n\n    *Query Strategy:* Since the new search results list titles like \"Simulations of the formation and substrate adhesion of PEI/\", I should craft queries to locate the full text or specific data from similar studies, as the current read list didn't capture the content.\n\n    *Let's build the JSON.*\n\n    *Wait, one constraint check:* \"You MUST respond with valid JSON only. No prose, no markdown, no code fences — just the JSON object.\"\n    *I need to make sure I don't include ```json at the start or end.*\n\n    *Content Check:*\n    *   Sub-questions: Break down the main question.\n    *   Gaps: Specific values, specific comparison studies.\n    *   Confidence: Low (due to lack of extracted facts).\n    *   Queries: Specific combinations.\n\n    *Let's assemble.*","input_tokens":2270,"output_tokens":2781,"reasoning_tokens":1797,"duration_ms":49465.271900000516,"cost_usd":0.004929},{"ts":"2026-03-12T02:06:41.535863+00:00","vid":"WEB_20260312T015506_435334","node":"structured","type":"llm_detail","call_type":"structured:PageSummaryBatch","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","temperature":0.5,"max_tokens":8192,"reasoning_enabled":false,"response_format":"","prompt_messages":[{"role":"system","content":"You MUST respond with valid JSON only. No prose, no markdown, no code fences — just the JSON object."},{"role":"user","content":"You are a research analyst reading web pages for a deep research project.\n\nRESEARCH QUESTION: What experimental evidence exists for divinyl sulfone (DVS) crosslinked polyethylenimine\n  (PEI/BPEI) adhesive coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene and aluminum oxide\n  substrates, and how do measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths compare with molecular\n  dynamics predictions of single-bond work of adhesion?\n\nRead the following 3 pages and create a research note for each.\n\n--- PAGE: (PDF) Plasma‐induced surface modification and adhesion ... ---\nURL: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/229902264_Plasma-induced_surface_modification_and_adhesion_enhancement_of_polypropylene_surface\nCONTENT:\n[ ](https://www.researchgate.net) # Security check required We've detected unusual activity from your network. To continue, complete the security check below. 驗證成功。正在等待 www.researchgate.net 回應 Ray ID: 9daf38d63b6e2724 Client IP: 216.232.201.117 © 2008-2026 ResearchGate GmbH. All rights reserved.\n\n--- PAGE: Enhancement of Polypropylene Bonding Through Plasma– ... ---\nURL: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11945717/\nCONTENT:\n[ Skip to main content ](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11945717/#main-content) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/us_flag.svg) An official website of the United States government Here's how you know Here's how you know ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-dot-gov.svg) **Official websites use .gov** A **.gov** website belongs to an official government organization in the United States. ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/icon-https.svg) **Secure .gov websites use HTTPS** A **lock** ( Lock Locked padlock icon ) or **https://** means you've safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites. [ ![NCBI home page](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/ncbi-logos/nih-nlm-ncbi--white.svg) ](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/) ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/search.svg) Search ![](https://cdn.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pd-medc-pmc-cloudpmc-viewer/production/a2b04810/var/data/static/img/p