 of the research question. It serves primarily as evidence that DVS crosslinking quantification is possible via sulfur content analysis. The absence of MD simulations in this biological context further widens the gap between available literature and the specific computational-experimental comparison sought in the research question. Researchers must look for industrial polymer literature rather than biomedical hydrogel studies to find the specific PEI/DVS adhesion metrics. The specific range of 0 to 100 mM DVS provides a benchmark for crosslinker concentration effects, though mechanical stability here refers to hydrogel integrity rather than interfacial adhesion strength. The focus on retinal pigment epithelial cellular responses underscores the biocompatibility focus, contrasting with the structural bonding focus of the research question. This divergence suggests that while DVS chemistry is well-documented in biomedicine, its application in high-strength structural adhesives on activated metals or plastics requires distinct investigation parameters not covered in this cytocompatibility study. The EPA HERO ID is 4690362.\n\n    *   *Word Count Check:*\n        *   Page 1: ~340 words.\n        *   Page 2: ~350 words.\n        *   Page 3: ~350 words.\n    *   *JSON Safety:* I will ensure no unescaped quotes. I will use `\\n` for line breaks if needed, but single paragraph blocks are safer for JSON. I will keep them as single long strings to avoid newline issues, or use `\\n` explicitly. I will use single long strings to minimize escape errors.\n\n    *   *Wait, one more thing:* The prompt asks for \"300-400 word deep analysis\". I need to be sure. I'll count roughly.\n    *   Page 1: \"This page represents...\" to \"...access restriction.\" -> ~340 words.\n    *   Page 2: \"This article provides...\" to \"...Wuhan University of Technology.\" -> ~360 words.\n    *   Page 3: \"This reference details...\" to \"...ID is 4690362.\" -> ~360 words.\n\n    *   *STORM Perspectives:* I will list them as an array of strings.\n    *   *Specific Facts:* Array of strings.\n    *   *Quantitative Results:* Array of strings (or object? Prompt says \"Any data tables... preserve exact numbers\". I'll use an array of strings for simplicity and validity).\n    *   *New Understanding:* String.\n\n    *   *Final check on JSON validity:* No trailing commas. Proper quoting.\n\n    *   *Let's assemble.*","input_tokens":5705,"output_tokens":8329,"reasoning_tokens":6343,"duration_ms":149245.0625000056,"cost_usd":0.014477},{"ts":"2026-03-12T02:07:31.966134+00:00","vid":"WEB_20260312T015506_435334","node":"structured","type":"llm_detail","call_type":"structured:AgenticRoundAnalysis","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","temperature":0.5,"max_tokens":4096,"reasoning_enabled":false,"response_format":"","prompt_messages":[{"role":"system","content":"You MUST respond with valid JSON only. No prose, no markdown, no code fences — just the JSON object."},{"role":"user","content":"You are a research search strategist conducting an agentic deep research loop.\n\nRESEARCH QUESTION: What experimental evidence exists for divinyl sulfone (DVS) crosslinked polyethylenimine\n  (PEI/BPEI) adhesive coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene and aluminum oxide\n  substrates, and how do measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths compare with molecular\n  dynamics predictions of single-bond work of adhesion?\n\nROUND HISTORY:\nRound 1: 9 queries -> 60 web + 0 academic, 56 new URLs, 3 pages read\nRound 2: 8 queries -> 59 web + 0 academic, 56 new URLs, 4 pages read\nRound 3: 7 queries -> 50 web + 0 academic, 41 new URLs, 3 pages read\n\nKNOWLEDGE ACQUIRED (10 pages read so far):\n[Page 1] Engineering Hydrogel Adhesion for Biomedical Applications via ...\n  Summary: Engineering Hydrogel Adhesion for Biomedical Applications via Chemical Design of the Junction | ACS Biomaterials Science & Engineering ACS ACS Publications C&EN CAS Find my institution Log In Quick View Share Share on F