structure and cytocompatibility of divinyl ...\n- [PDF] POLYMER GRAFTING AND CROSSLINKING\n- Cu(i) stabilizing crosslinked polyethyleneimine\n- [PDF] Modified Poly(ethylene imines) for plasmid delivery\n- [PDF] Activated Gas Plasma Surface Treatment of Polymers for Adhesive ...\n- [PDF] Effect of Atmospheric Pressure Nonequilibrium Plasma Pretreatment ...\n- Enhanced toxicity of the protein cross-linkers divinyl sulfone and ...\n- Experimental Design of the Adhesion between a PEI/Glass Fiber ...\n- Plasma-Enhanced Chemical Vapor Deposition (PE-CVD) yields ...\n- A Comprehensive Review on plant and animal fiber reinforced ...\n- (PDF) Experimental Design of the Adhesion between a PEI/Glass ...\n- [PDF] Deposition of Alumina Coatings from Nanopowders by Plasma ...\n- Analysis of Plasma Electrolytic Oxidation Process Parameters for ...\n- Effect of Plasma Treatment on Coating Adhesion and Tensile ...\n- (PDF) Plasma Electrolysis Spraying Al2O3 Coating onto Quartz ...\n- Dissimilar material bonding technology for lightweight future mobility\n- [PDF] Advances in structural adhesive bonding\n\nPERSPECTIVE COVERAGE:\n  Covered (3/9): Scientific, Regulatory, Industry\n  Uncovered: Economic, Public_Health, Historical, Regional, Methodological, Emerging_Trends\n  Low coverage: Scientific, Regulatory, Industry\n\nBased on what has been READ:\n1. Decompose the research question into 5-8 sub-questions.\n   Which sub-questions have ZERO or WEAK evidence?\n   Which sub-questions are well-answered with strong evidence?\n2. What CONTRADICTIONS exist between sources? Flag conflicting evidence.\n3. What specific KNOWLEDGE GAPS remain? List them as specific factual questions\n   we CANNOT yet answer. 'none' is almost never correct for a complex research question.\n4. Rate overall confidence in accumulated knowledge: LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH with reasoning.\n5. Which perspectives need more coverage?\n6. Generate 3-6 targeted WEB queries to fill those gaps.\n7. Generate 1-3 ACADEMIC queries using precise terminology.\n8. Optionally generate 0-1 semantic EXA queries.\n9. Assess ANSWER COMPLETENESS for the research question:\n   - List specific sub-questions that remain UNANSWERED.\n   - For each answered sub-question, rate evidence strength (weak/moderate/strong).\n   - 'expanding': Major sub-questions still unanswered.\n   - 'narrowing': Most sub-questions answered, seeking confirmation/depth.\n   - 'saturated': All sub-questions answered with strong evidence.\n10. Should we continue searching?\n\nFocus on queries that address content-level gaps, not just missing URLs."}],"response_content":"{\n  \"sub_questions\": [\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Does experimental evidence exist for DVS-crosslinked PEI coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Does experimental evidence exist for DVS-crosslinked PEI coatings on plasma-activated aluminum oxide?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"What are the measured peel strengths for DVS-PEI on plasma-treated substrates?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"What are the measured lap-shear strengths for DVS-PEI on plasma-treated substrates?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"Do molecular dynamics predictions exist for single-bond work of adhesion for PEI-DVS interfaces?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"WEAK\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"How do experimental adhesion values compare quantitatively to MD predictions?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"ZERO\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"question\": \"What is the chemical mechanism of DVS-PEI bonding to plasma-functionalized surfaces?\",\n      \"evidence_status\": \"WEAK\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"contradictions\": [],\n  \"knowledge_gaps\": [\n    \"No specific data found linking DVS crosslinker specifically to PEI adhesive coatings (most literature is DVS-Hyaluronic Acid hydrogels).\",\n    \"No experimental peel or lap-shear strength values identified for PEI/DVS on polypropylene or aluminum oxide.\",\n    \"No identified studies comparing macroscopic adhesion strength of PEI coatings to molecular dynamics work of adhesion predictions.\",\n    \"Unclear if plasma activation parameters (power, gas, time) for PP/Al2O3 are optimized for PEI/DVS chemistry in existing literature.\",\n    \"Missing information on whether DVS-PEI forms covalent bonds with plasma-generated hydroxyl/amine groups on PP/Al2O3.\"\n  ],\n  \"confidence_rating\": \"LOW\",\n  \"confidence_reasoning\": \"Of 10 pages read, none contained specific data for the DVS-PEI-PP/Al2O3 system. Most results concern Hyaluronic Acid crosslinking or generic plasma treatment without the specific adhesive chemistry. New search result titles suggest potential relevance but content is unverified.\",\n  \"perspectives_needed\": [\n    \"Methodological\",\n    \"Scientific\",\n    \"Emerging_Trends\"\n  ],\n  \"web_queries\": [\n    \"divinyl sulfone polyethylenimine adhesive coating adhesion strength\",\n    \"PEI DVS crosslinked plasma polypropylene lap shear test\",\n    \"molecular dynamics simulation PEI adhesion work of adhesion substrate\",\n    \"plasma activated aluminum oxide PEI coating adhesion mechanism\",\n    \"divinyl sulfone crosslinker PEI aluminum bonding strength\"\n  ],\n  \"academic_queries\": [\n    \"polyethylenimine divinyl sulfone interface adhesion energy simulation\",\n    \"plasma treated polypropylene polyethylenimine coating shear strength\",\n    \"work of adhesion molecular dynamics polyethylenimine substrate\"\n  ],\n  \"exa_queries\": [\n    \"experimental vs molecular dynamics adhesion strength PEI coating DVS crosslinker\"\n  ],\n  \"answer_completeness\": {\n    \"status\": \"expanding\",\n    \"unanswered_sub_questions\": [\n      \"Experimental evidence for DVS-PEI on plasma-PP\",\n      \"Experimental evidence for DVS-PEI on plasma-Al2O3\",\n      \"Measured peel strengths\",\n      \"Measured lap-shear strengths\",\n      \"Comparison of experimental vs MD predictions\"\n    ],\n    \"answered_sub_questions\": [],\n    \"evidence_strength_summary\": \"All core sub-questions currently have ZERO or WEAK evidence. The specific combination of materials and comparison methodology is not represented in the 10 pages read.\"\n  },\n  \"continue_search\": true\n}","response_reasoning":"Thinking Process:\n\n1.  **Analyze the Request:**\n    *   **Role:** Research search strategist conducting an agentic deep research loop.\n    *   **Task:** Respond with valid JSON only (no prose, no markdown, no code fences).\n    *   **Input:** Research question about DVS-crosslinked PEI adhesive coatings on plasma-activated PP and Al2O3, comparing experimental adhesion strengths with MD predictions.\n    *   **Context:** Round 3 of search. 10 pages read so far (mostly generic or irrelevant based on summaries). New search results provided (titles only).\n    *   **Output Requirements:** JSON object containing specific fields (sub-questions, contradictions, gaps, confidence, perspectives, queries, completeness, continuation decision).\n\n2.  **Evaluate Current Knowledge (based on \"KNOWLEDGE ACQUIRED\"):**\n    *   *Page 1:* Hydrogel adhesion biomedical (generic).\n    *   *Page 2:* MDPI Polymers issue list (generic).\n    *   *Page 3:* Lap shear strength prediction (Epoxy, not PEI/DVS).\n    *   *Page 4:* DVS crosslinking (ResearchGate security block, likely HA or generic).\n    *   *Page 5:* Crosslinking PEI (MDPI, title suggests relevance but summary is generic nav).\n    *   *Page 6:* Structure/cytocompatibility DVS crosslinked HA (not PEI/PP/Al).\n    *   *Page 7:* Patent DVS crosslinking HA (not PEI/PP/Al).\n    *   *Page 8:* Plasma-induced surface modification (ResearchGate block).\n    *   *Page 9:* Enhancement of PP bonding through Plasma (PMC, likely relevant to PP plasma but need to check PEI/DVS).\n    *   *Page 10:* DVS crosslinked HA cytocompatibility (duplicate/similar to Page 6).\n    *   *Overall Assessment:* The 10 pages read so far provide *very little* specific evidence for the exact combination: DVS + PEI + Plasma-PP/Al2O3 + Adhesion Strength vs. MD Predictions. Most results are about Hyaluronic Acid (HA) crosslinking with DVS, or generic plasma treatment of PP, or generic PEI crosslinking. The specific intersection is missing.\n\n3.  **Decompose Research Question:**\n    *   Q1: Does experimental evidence exist for DVS-crosslinked PEI coatings on plasma-activated PP?\n    *   Q2: Does experimental evidence exist for DVS-crosslinked PEI coatings on plasma-activated Al2O3?\n    *   Q3: What are the measured peel strengths for these systems?\n    *   Q4: What are the measured lap-shear strengths for these systems?\n    *   Q5: Do MD predictions exist for single-bond work of adhesion for PEI-DVS-substrate interfaces?\n    *   Q6: How do experimental values compare to MD predictions (correlation factor)?\n    *   Q7: What is the specific chemical mechanism of DVS-PEI bonding to plasma-treated surfaces?\n\n4.  **Identify Gaps & Contradictions:**\n    *   *Gaps:* Almost everything. The specific combination (DVS-PEI on Plasma-PP/Al2O3) is highly specific. Most literature found is DVS-HA (biomedical hydrogels) or PEI-glutaraldehyde, or Plasma-PP-epoxy.\n    *   *Contradictions:* None identified yet because insufficient data exists to contradict.\n    *   *Confidence:* LOW. The summaries indicate generic matches, not specific data points.\n\n5.  **Plan Next Queries:**\n    *   Need to target the specific chemical interface: PEI + DVS + Substrate (PP/Aluminum).\n    *   Need to target the simulation aspect: Molecular Dynamics + Adhesion + PEI.\n    *   Need to bypass the \"HA\" noise (DVS is heavily used for HA hydrogels).\n    *   Need to look for \"interfacial adhesion\" specifically, not just \"crosslinking\".\n\n6.  **Drafting the JSON:**\n    *   Ensure strict JSON validity (escape quotes, no trailing commas).\n    *   Follow the schema implied by the prompt's instructions (sub-questions, contradictions, gaps, confidence, perspectives, queries, completeness, continue).\n\n    *   *Sub-questions:* List 5-8.\n    *   *Evidence Status:* Mark most as ZERO/WEAK.\n    *   *Contradictions:* None yet.\n    *   *Gaps:* Specific adhesion values, MD comparison, specific substrate prep.\n    *   *Confidence:* LOW.\n    *   *Perspectives:* Scientific (needs more), Methodological (needs more).\n    *   *Queries:* Focus on \"PEI DVS adhesion\", \"PEI plasma polypropylene shear\", \"Molecular dynamics PEI adhesion work\", \"Divinyl sulfone PEI coating aluminum\".\n    *   *Completeness:* Expanding (major sub-questions unanswered).\n    *   *Continue:* Yes.\n\n7.  **Refining Queries:**\n    *   Web: \"divinyl sulfone polyethylenimine adhesion strength\", \"PEI DVS coating plasma polypropylene shear\", \"molecular dynamics simulation PEI adhesion work of adhesion\".\n    *   Academic: \"polyethylenimine divinyl sulfone interface adhesion\", \"plasma treated polypropylene PEI coating lap shear\".\n    *   Exa: \"PEI DVS crosslinked adhesive coating experimental vs simulation\".\n\n8.  **Final JSON Construction:**\n    *   Check for special characters.\n    *   Ensure no markdown formatting outside the JSON structure (the prompt says \"respond with valid JSON only\").\n\n    *Self-Correction on JSON Structure:* The prompt asks for specific sections based on the numbered list (1-10). I should structure the JSON keys to reflect these analysis points clearly.\n    Keys: `sub_questions`, `contradictions`, `knowledge_gaps`, `confidence_rating`, `confidence_reasoning`, `perspectives_needed`, `web_queries`, `academic_queries`, `exa_queries`, `answer_completeness`, `continue_search`.\n\n    *Wait, one constraint:* \"You MUST respond with valid JSON only. No prose, no markdown, no code fences — just the JSON object.\"\n    I must ensure the output is raw JSON text.\n\n    *Content Check:*\n    *   Sub-questions: Break down the main question.\n    *   Evidence status: Be honest (mostly weak/zero).\n    *   Gaps: Specific data points missing.\n    *   Confidence: Low.\n    *   Queries: Targeted to fill gaps.\n    *   Completeness: Expanding.\n\n    *Let's build the JSON content.*\n    *   `sub_questions`: Array of objects with question and evidence_status.\n    *   `contradictions`: Array of strings (empty if none).\n    *   `knowledge_gaps`: Array of strings.\n    *   `confidence_rating`: \"LOW\".\n    *   `confidence_reasoning`: String.\n    *   `perspectives_needed`: Array of strings.\n    *   `web_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `academic_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `exa_queries`: Array of strings.\n    *   `answer_completeness`: Object with status and details.\n    *   `continue_search`: Boolean.\n\n    *Refining the \"Knowledge Acquired\" analysis:* The summaries provided in the prompt for the 10 pages are mostly navigational pages or irrelevant (HA instead of PEI). This confirms the LOW confidence. The New Search Results titles show some promise (e.g., \"Enhancement of Polypropylene Bonding Through Plasma–...\", \"Experimental Design of the Adhesion between a PEI/Glass Fiber...\"). These need to be investigated in Round 4.\n\n    *Query Strategy:* The previous queries might have been too broad or hit the \"HA\" noise. Need to explicitly exclude HA or focus on \"adhesive coating\" rather than \"hydrogel\".\n\n    *Final check on JSON syntax:* Escape double quotes inside strings. No comments.\n\n    *Let's assemble.*","input_tokens":2781,"output_tokens":2737,"reasoning_tokens":1817,"duration_ms":50269.70009999786,"cost_usd":0.004993},{"ts":"2026-03-12T02:11:45.422966+00:00","vid":"WEB_20260312T015506_435334","node":"structured","type":"llm_detail","call_type":"structured:PageSummaryBatch","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","temperature":0.5,"max_tokens":8192,"reasoning_enabled":false,"response_format":"","prompt_messages":[{"role":"system","content":"You MUST respond with valid JSON only. No prose, no markdown, no code fences — just the JSON object."},{"role":"user","content":"You are a research analyst reading web pages for a deep research project.\n\nRESEARCH QUESTION: What experimental evidence exists for divinyl sulfone (DVS) crosslinked polyethylenimine\n  (PEI/BPEI) adhesive coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene and aluminum oxide\n  substrates, and how do measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths compare with molecular\n  dynamics predictions of single-bond work of adhesion?\n\nRead the following 3 pages and create a research note for each.\n\n--- PAGE: Surface treatment of poly(p-phenylene sulfide) and its impact on ... ---\nURL: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/380945318_Surface_treatment_of_polyp-phenylene_sulfide_and_its_impact_on_adhesion_of_epoxy_resin_Theoretical_insights\nCONTENT:\n[ ](https://www.researchgate.net) # Security check required We've detected unusual activity from your network. To continue, complete the security check below. 驗證成功。正在等待 www.researchgate.net 回應 Ray ID: 9daf3f2499a92ae2 Client IP: 216.232.201.117 © 2008-2026 ResearchGate GmbH. All rights reserved.\n\n--- PAGE: Adhesion Bonding of Polyphenylene Sulfide - Plastics Decorating ---\nURL: https://plasticsdecorating.com/enews/2013/adhesion-bonding-of-polyphenylene-sulfide/\nCONTENT:\n* [ [![Corotec](https://cdn.broadstreetads.com/assets/77c8bc2a-89dc-4df1-af63-8005f4bcc954.png)](https://corotec.com/products/plasma-jet/?source=Pdecorating-2026 \"Corotec\")](https://plasticsdecorating.com/enews/2013/adhesion-bonding-of-polyphenylene-sulfide/) * [Home](https://plasticsdecorating.com/) * [Article Archive](https://plasticsdecorating.com/enews/2013/adhesion-bonding-of-polyphenylene-sulfide/) * [Article Archive](https://plasticsdecorating.com/article-archive/) * [Digital Archive](https://plasticsdecorating.com/article-archive/digital-archive/) * [ENews Archive](https://plasticsdecor