ences).\n    *   Input: Research question, Round history (4 rounds so far), Knowledge Acquired (13 pages read summaries), New Search Results (titles only), Perspective Coverage, and specific instructions (1-10).\n    *   Research Question: What experimental evidence exists for divinyl sulfone (DVS) crosslinked polyethylenimine (PEI/BPEI) adhesive coatings on plasma-activated polypropylene and aluminum oxide substrates, and how do measured peel or lap-shear adhesion strengths compare with molecular dynamics predictions of single-bond work of adhesion?\n    *   Constraint: Valid JSON only.\n\n2.  **Evaluate Current Knowledge (13 pages read):**\n    *   Page 1: Hydrogel adhesion biomedical (general).\n    *   Page 2: MDPI Polymers issue (general).\n    *   Page 3: Prediction of Lap Shear Strength (Epoxy, not PEI/DVS).\n    *   Page 4: DVS crosslinking (ResearchGate security block, likely HA not PEI).\n    *   Page 5: Crosslinking Approaches for PEI (MDPI, promising title but summary generic).\n    *   Page 6: Structure/cytocompatibility DVS crosslinked HA (not PEI/PP/AlOx).\n    *   Page 7: Patent DVS crosslinking HA (not PEI).\n    *   Page 8: Plasma-induced surface modification (ResearchGate security block).\n    *   Page 9: Enhancement of Polypropylene Bonding Through Plasma (PMC, promising for PP plasma).\n    *   Page 10: DVS cross-linked hyaluronic acid (not PEI).\n    *   Page 11: Surface treatment PPS (ResearchGate security block).\n    *   Page 12: Adhesion Bonding PPS (not PP/PEI/DVS).\n    *   Page 13: Solvent-free adhesive (Nature, general).\n    *   *Critical Observation:* Most read pages are about Hyaluronic Acid (HA) crosslinked with DVS, or general plasma treatment of PP, or PPS (Polyphenylene Sulfide). There is very little specific evidence read so far regarding *PEI/BPEI crosslinked with DVS* specifically on *plasma-activated PP and Aluminum Oxide*. The specific combination (DVS + PEI + Plasma PP/AlOx + MD comparison) seems largely unaddressed in the *read* content. Many links were security blocks (ResearchGate).\n\n3.  **Address Instructions (1-10):**\n\n    *   **1. Decompose & Evidence Status:**\n        *   Sub-q1: Existence of DVS-crosslinked PEI adhesives? (Weak/None in read content, mostly HA).\n        *   Sub-q2: Application on plasma-activated PP? (Weak, Page 9 discusses PP plasma but not PEI/DVS coating).\n        *   Sub-q3: Application on Aluminum Oxide? (None).\n        *   Sub-q4: Measured peel/lap-shear strengths? (None specific to this system).\n        *   Sub-q5: MD predictions of single-bond work of adhesion? (None).\n        *   Sub-q6: Comparison between experiment and MD? (None).\n        *   *Zero/Weak:* All specific combinations.\n        *   *Well-answered:* General DVS crosslinking chemistry (HA), General PP plasma treatment.\n\n    *   **2. Contradictions:** None identified yet due to lack of specific data.\n\n    *   **3. Knowledge Gaps:**\n        *   Does DVS crosslink PEI specifically for adhesion (vs HA for hydrogels)?\n        *   Are there specific studies on PEI/DVS on AlOx?\n        *   Are there MD simulations correlating to PEI/DVS adhesion experiments?\n        *   What are the specific shear strength values (MPa) for this system?\n\n    *   **4. Confidence Rating:** LOW. The read content is mostly tangential (HA instead of PEI, PPS instead of PP, general plasma instead of specific coating).\n\n    *   **5. Perspectives:** Scientific (needs more specific chemistry/adhesion data), Methodological (MD vs Experiment comparison).\n\n    *   **6. Web Queries:** Need to target the specific chemical combination and the MD comparison.\n        *   \"divinyl sulfone polyethylenimine adhesive\"\n        *   \"PEI DVS crosslinking adhesion strength\"\n        *   \"polyethylenimine coating aluminum oxide adhesion\"\n        *   \"molecular dynamics work of adhesion PEI substrate\"\n        *   \"plasma treated polypropylene PEI coating adhesion\"\n\n    *   **7. Academic Queries:** Use precise terms.\n        *   \"divinyl sulfone\" AND \"polyethylenimine\" AND \"adhesion\"\n        *   \"PEI\" AND \"DVS\" AND \"lap shear\" OR \"peel strength\"\n        *   \"molecular dynamics\" AND \"work of adhesion\" AND \"polyethylenimine\"\n\n    *   **8. EXA Queries:** Optional, maybe skip to save space/keep JSON clean, or use one for deep semantic match. Let's include one for the MD comparison aspect.\n\n    *   **9. Answer Completeness:**\n        *   Unanswered: Almost all specific sub-questions.\n        *   Evidence Strength: Weak for general components, None for the specific system.\n        *   Status: 'expanding'.\n\n    *   **10. Continue Searching:** Yes, definitely. The core combination hasn't been found in the 13 pages read.\n\n4.  **Drafting the JSON:**\n    *   Ensure strict JSON syntax (quotes, commas, no trailing commas).\n    *   Escape special characters if necessary.\n    *   No markdown formatting (```json ... ```).\n\n5.  **Refining Queries:**\n    *   Make sure they aren't just repeats of previous rounds (though I don't see the previous queries listed, I must infer from the results that general terms were used). The results show lots of HA and PPS. I need to force PEI and AlOx.\n    *   Query 1: \"divinyl sulfone\" \"polyethylenimine\" adhesive\n    *   Query 2: PEI DVS crosslinking adhesion strength\n    *   Query 3: polyethylenimine coating aluminum oxide adhesion\n    *   Query 4: molecular dynamics work of adhesion PEI substrate\n    *   Query 5: plasma treated polypropylene PEI coating adhesion\n    *   Academic 1: \"divinyl sulfone\" AND \"polyethylenimine\" AND \"adhesion\"\n    *   Academic 2: \"PEI\" AND \"DVS\" AND \"lap shear\" OR \"peel strength\"\n    *   Academic 3: \"molecular dynamics\" AND \"work of adhesion\" AND \"polyethylenimine\"\n\n6.  **Final Review against Constraints:**\n    *   Valid JSON only.\n    *   No prose.\n    *   No markdown.\n    *   Address all 10 points in the structure.\n\n    *Self-Correction 