ntroduced onto the surface of polymers by plasma activation. In the case of inert polymers, the plasma-induced functional ...","A low-temperature, atmospheric pressure helium and oxygen plasma has been used for the surface preparation of aluminum 2024 prior to adhesive bonding. The ...","In order to improve UHMWPE fiber/polymer matrix bonding, fibers should be subject to the appropriate surface treatment. A variety of surface ...","This study focuses on the molecular interactions between PVAc and aluminum or beech wood influenced by plasma surface modification.","Plasma activation is a surface modification technique that prepares materials for bonding, gluing, coating, and printing by increasing surface energy.","This paper presents the results of simple adhesive lap joint shear strength tests of materials under atmospheric plasma treatment conditions ...","This study explored the enhancement of the bonding strength in metal–polymer hy- brid structures through plasma treatment of metal surfaces and ...","aluminum oxide (531.38 eV) and 40.9% magnesium oxide (532.18 eV), but after the plasma treatment a significant amount of magnesium oxide migrated to the ...","Aluminum particles (Al) inherently contain a natural oxide (Al2O3) coating that limits rates of diffusion- controlled energy release and can prevent ...","The Sabreen Group offers comprehensive onsite education and training on adhesion bonding processes, plasma pretreatment and advanced manufacturing techniques."]},{"ts":"2026-03-12T02:16:10.479511+00:00","vid":"WEB_20260312T015506_435334","node":"search","type":"search_result","engine":"serper","query":"PEI DVS crosslinking mechanism adhesion","result_count":10,"urls":["https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35870776/","https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0032386118304142","https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Crosslinking-polymerization-of-PEI-and-DBA_fig2_376325570","https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/acsabm.0c01300","https://journals.sagepub.com/d