config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:111:    reason: "Could be clinical (drug efficacy) or policy (insurance coverage / cost-effectiveness). Without disambiguation the inductor must not silently pick one."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:114:    query: "What are the safety, efficacy, and regulatory landscape for AI-driven clinical decision-support tools in primary care?"
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:116:    reason: "Spans clinical AI (evidence base), regulatory (FDA SaMD), tech (ML reliability). No single template covers; operator must split."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:121:    reason: "Crosses clinical (obesity efficacy) and policy (Medicare coverage decision). No template currently covers obesity-specific clinical contract."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:126:    reason: "Too broad — no specific drug, comparator, or outcome named. Cannot route to clinical_tirzepatide_t2dm (which is tirzepatide-specific) without operator scoping."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:136:    reason: "Combines T2DM clinical question with cardiology overlay. No CV-comorbidity template; operator must scope further."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:141:    reason: "Crosses clinical (GLP-1 indications) and policy (IRA / Medicare access). Both templates partially apply; needs operator decomposition."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:144:    query: "Compare clinical evidence and pricing for tirzepatide"
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:146:    reason: "Two-part query (clinical evidence + pricing) crosses templates. Operator must split into two independent runs."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:156:    reason: "On-domain adversarial: mentions 'semaglutide' (clinical_tirzepatide_t2dm support keyword) but the question is about obesity in non-diabetic patients, not the T2DM contract. No tirzepatide anchor present."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:161:    reason: "On-domain adversarial: 'Ozempic' is in the clinical support keywords as a comparator, but the question is non-T2DM weight-loss safety. The clinical_tirzepatide_t2dm contract doesn't cover this scope."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:181:    reason: "On-domain adversarial: 'type 2 diabetes' + 'diabetes' match clinical support keywords but no specific drug anchor (tirzepatide / Mounjaro / SURPASS) is named. The query is too broad for the tirzepatide-specific contract."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:205:    reason: "Mental-health clinical area. Outside the tirzepatide/T2DM template. M-NEW or M-D6 might add psychiatric clinical templates eventually."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:210:    reason: "Economic policy / social science. Outside both Medicare drug-price and clinical templates."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:215:    reason: "Vaccine clinical area, distinct from T2DM template. Pharmacovigilance retrieval adapter (M-D6 candidate) not built."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:230:    reason: "Gene therapy / ophthalmology clinical area. Outside T2DM template."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:245:    reason: "ML research / technical literature. Tech domain has no current curated template."
config\auto_induction\validation_set.yaml:255:    reason: "Pharmacogenomics / cardiology clinical question. Outside T2DM template; would need a separate clinical template."
