# Clinical domain scope template — HONEST-REBUILD Phase 2c.
#
# Used when the user is researching drug efficacy, safety, mechanism,
# clinical guidelines, meta-analyses, or treatment comparisons. The
# corpus should be dominated by peer-reviewed primary studies (T1)
# and systematic reviews (T2), with regulatory documents (T3) as the
# authoritative source for labelled indications and safety warnings.
#
# Industry marketing / HCP-portal sources (T5) are allowed but capped
# at <=15% and must not dominate any section. Commentary / blog (T6)
# and conference abstracts / preprints (T7) are allowed only as
# supporting or hypothesis-generating evidence.

domain: clinical
description: >
  Peer-reviewed-primary-evidence-dominant corpus for clinical research.
  Follows PRISMA-style inclusion / exclusion patterns.

# Default PICO framing overrides. The scope gate will attempt heuristic
# extraction from the query first; these are fallback defaults.
pico_defaults:
  comparator: placebo or standard of care

# Inclusion criteria surfaced to the user in the pre-registered protocol.
inclusion_criteria:
  - Peer-reviewed journal article indexed in PubMed / OpenAlex / Semantic Scholar.
  - Human studies.
  - Published in English, or with a certified English translation.
  - Reports quantitative outcomes (efficacy, safety, PK/PD, or QoL).
  - Regulatory documents (FDA/EMA/Health Canada/MHRA/TGA/PMDA/NMPA) when
    discussing labelled indications, contraindications, or safety warnings.

# Exclusion criteria surfaced to the user in the pre-registered protocol.
exclusion_criteria:
  - User-upload document hosts (Scribd, SlideShare, ResearchGate) unless
    the document is also available at the original issuer's URL.
  - Student journals (high school journals, undergraduate journals).
  - Press releases from pharmaceutical manufacturers without a peer-reviewed
    primary source to corroborate claims.
  - Blog posts and law-firm commentary used as primary evidence (allowed as
    supplementary context only).
  - In vitro and animal-only studies when the research question is human-
    clinical (allowed for mechanistic sections only).

# Expected final-corpus tier distribution. The corpus-approval gate
# (Phase 2g) checks actual retrieval against this and shows the delta
# to the user.
expected_tier_distribution:
  - tier: T1
    min_fraction: 0.30
    max_fraction: 0.60
    rationale: >
      Peer-reviewed primary studies (RCTs, cohort, case-control) are the
      foundation of clinical efficacy and safety claims.
  - tier: T2
    min_fraction: 0.15
    max_fraction: 0.40
    rationale: >
      Systematic reviews and meta-analyses consolidate primary evidence
      and are the preferred source for magnitude estimates.
  - tier: T3
    min_fraction: 0.05
    max_fraction: 0.25
    rationale: >
      Regulatory documents (FDA labels, EMA EPARs, Health Canada monographs)
      are authoritative for labelled indications and safety warnings.
  - tier: T4
    min_fraction: 0.00
    max_fraction: 0.20
    rationale: >
      Narrative reviews and clinical guideline articles — useful for
      context and mechanism, but not for novel efficacy claims.
  - tier: T5
    min_fraction: 0.00
    max_fraction: 0.15
    rationale: >
      Industry HCP portals and marketing pages — allowed for labelled
      claims that are already corroborated by T3 regulatory sources.
  - tier: T6
    min_fraction: 0.00
    max_fraction: 0.10
    rationale: >
      Commentary, news, and blog posts — allowed only as context,
      not as primary evidence.
  - tier: T7
    min_fraction: 0.00
    max_fraction: 0.10
    rationale: >
      Conference abstracts and preprints — hypothesis-generating only.
      Should not dominate a systematic review corpus.

